# Local private env template for Diary + User Portrait demo.
# Copy values into `.env.local` or export them in your shell.
# Do not commit real keys.

# MiniMax one-env preset. This enables Diary + User Portrait server-side LLM:
# - server-side chat-completions compatible LLM calls
# - server-side MiniMax TTS bridge
# - browser-safe fallback if the provider fails
MINIMAX_API_KEY=${MINIMAX_API_KEY}

# Optional: force the frontend to use the local Vite dev API bridge for Diary.
# If omitted, Diary still uses the mock service, whose reaction/TTS methods call
# `/api/diary/reactions` and `/api/diary/tts` as a safe enhancement.
# VITE_DIARY_API_MODE=http
# VITE_DIARY_API_BASE_URL=/api/diary

# Optional: force User Portrait to use the local Vite dev API bridge.
# VITE_PORTRAIT_API_MODE=http
# VITE_PORTRAIT_API_BASE_URL=/api/portrait

# Optional MiniMax overrides. Leave commented unless the defaults need changing.
# DIARY_LLM_PRESET=minimax
# DIARY_LLM_MODEL=MiniMax-M2.7
# DIARY_REACTION_MODEL=MiniMax-M2.7
# DIARY_LLM_RESPONSE_FORMAT=none
# DIARY_TTS_PROVIDER=minimax
# DIARY_TTS_MODEL=speech-2.8-hd
# DIARY_TTS_VOICE=Chinese (Mandarin)_Cute_Spirit
# DIARY_TTS_AUDIO_FORMAT=mp3
